### GRAVEYARD Lessons (8 Entries - Mistakes to AVOID)

| # | Category | Lesson | Rule |
|---|----------|--------|------|
| 1 | ResourceError | HCO CR field casing | Always verify CRD schema before patching |
| 2 | TypeError | Wrong type hints on DynamicClient | Always use `DynamicClient` from `kubernetes.dynamic` |
| 3 | ResourceError | Multiple class-scoped VMs cause scheduling failures | Each distinct VM fixture in its own class |
| 4 | AssertionError | `run_virtctl_command` returns False on stderr logs | Pass `verify_stderr=False` for virtctl commands |
| 5 | TypeError | `ocp_resources` re-raises `ApiException` not `TimeoutExpiredError` | Catch `ApiException` for K8s API errors |
| 6 | LogicError | Reset on paused VMI succeeds (not an error) | Verify actual KubeVirt API behavior before writing negative tests |
| 7 | LogicError | `unprivileged_client` is namespace admin with broad permissions | Verify RBAC scope before writing RBAC negative tests |
| 8 | TimeoutError | SSH timeout too short after hard reset | Use `TIMEOUT_10MIN` for cold boots |
| 9 | **ResourceError** | **VM with `maxSockets=8` + `4Gi` memory exceeds cluster resources** | **Use `maxSockets=4`, `memory_guest=VM_MEMORY_GUEST` ("2Gi")** |
| 10 | **ResourceError** | **CPU hotplug migration fails on constrained clusters** | **Negative tests (webhook rejection) work without migration; don't depend on positive hotplug tests** |
| 11 | TimeoutError | Reset on paused VMI keeps it paused | Don't call `wait_for_running_vm` after reset on paused VMI |

**Entries 9 and 10 are directly relevant to the CPU hotplug max sockets tests being generated.** They document failures from a previous attempt at this exact feature.
